title: For Sale:  WWII WW2 US Remington Model 11 Military Riot Shotgun "Property US Navy"
location: Southwest Little Rock, Little Rock, Arkansas
postcontent: Up for sale is an original WWII US Remington Model 11 Military Riot Shotgun (12 gauge).  On the receiver is the US Ordnance "flaming bomb" and "US" marking on the top left.  What makes this shotgun even more rare is that it was a contract weapon for the US Navy and so the top of the barrel is stamped "Property US Navy."  The Remington factory code on the barrel dates this shotgun to "July 1942."  This is a real deal wartime shotgun acquired by the US Navy.  The shotgun was most likely acquired by the US Navy under the "Blanket Procurement Program" as it has the game scene engraved on the receiver for commercial production and the smooth blued finish but then was acquired by the military.  According to Bruce Canfield and his book "United States Combat Shotguns" only around 2300 Remington Model 11 shotguns were ever acquired by the US Navy for use in WWII.  Thus, this is 1 of only 2300 Remington Model 11 "Property US Navy" shotguns in WWII.  The bore is bright and shiny with no pitting.  No cracks in the wood.  Excellent finish on the receiver and barrel.  Please E-mail if you are interested.  I will ship the shotgun anywhere in the country to include $25-$30 shipping depending upon location.  I will meet face to face in Arkansas.  Thank you!
